{"questionId":"22269674","questionHtml":"<p>Sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> on the following pair of axes.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/ee741a0781e03147586089cef4f87b2601b7f6f7.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e34e43f42a03b05b967f9fbfbeca68951ea3f968.png\" width=\"483\" height=\"269\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> smooth curve, through origin, with maximum in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>1</mn><mi>st</mi></msup></math> quadrant and minimum in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>3</mn><mi>rd</mi></msup></math> quadrant (approximately correct position).</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> correct (approximate) position of endpoints and rotational symmetry. Condone a (small) gap between end of curve and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22269674","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.10a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Sketch the graph of y=fx on the following pair of axes.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}